SYNOPSIS
        status remove_armour(int ibFlags)

DEFINED IN
        armour.c

DESCRIPTION
        Attempts to remove a piece of armour from a living. Returns 1
        on success and 0 on failure. The passed flags can be used to
        bypass failure checks and otherwise modify removal behavior.
        See armour.h for macros to use as flags.

EXAMPLE
        remove_armour(A_REMOVE_IGNORE_COMMAND_COSTS|A_REMOVE_SILENT)
        will silently remove armour without checking to see if the
        wearer has enough command points remaining.
